<p>I have a XML that contains data like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt; &lt;posts&gt;   &lt;row Id="1" PostTypeId="1"         AcceptedAnswerId="15" CreationDate="2010-07-19T19:12:12.510" Score="27"         ViewCount="1647" Body="some text;" OwnerUserId="8"         LastActivityDate="2010-09-15T21:08:26.077"         Title="title" AnswerCount="5" CommentCount="1" FavoriteCount="17" /&gt; [...] </code></pre>  <p>(The dataset is a <a href="https://archive.org/download/stackexchange/stats.stackexchange.com.7z" rel="nofollow">dump from stats.stackexchange.com</a>)</p>  <p>How to get a data.frame with the attributes "Id" and "PostTypeId"?</p>  <p>I have been trying with the XML library but I get to a point where I don't know how to unwrap the values:</p>  <pre><code>library(XML)  xml &lt;- xmlTreeParse("Posts.xml",useInternalNode=TRUE) types &lt;- getNodeSet(xml, '//row/@PostTypeId')  &gt; types[1] [[1]] PostTypeId         "1"  attr(,"class") [1] "XMLAttributeValue" </code></pre>  <p>Which would be the proper R way of getting a projection of those two columns from the XML into a data.frame?</p>